<subSubSection pageId="109" pageNumber="867" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="109.[118,1329,286,947]" pageId="109" pageNumber="867">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[121,477,597,630]" pageId="109" pageNumber="867">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. Known only from five localities and previously classified as Vulnerable, but the species is suspected to be more abundant and has been reclassified as Data Deficient. Old reports of similar species such as Christie’s Long-eared Bat (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1838" box="[862,983,716,749]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Plecotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="109" pageNumber="867" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="christii">P. christii</taxonomicName>
) may need reviewing to check for misidentifications. Very poorly known overall;likely to be affected by habitat loss due to timber extraction and agriculture expansion.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
